oc:kn_0459029e a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing any plugin with more than 3 capabilities" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Organize plugins by function with multi-level directories: commands/ for user-facing operations, agents/ for autonomous orchestrators, skills/ for domain knowledge, hooks/ for lifecycle automation, lib/ for shared code, servers/ for MCP servers, config/ for environment settings." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Multi-level organization scales to enterprise complexity and keeps related concerns grouped logically." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_12b453d4 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:SecurityImplication ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building plugins that handle sensitive infrastructure or production environments" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Implement layered security hooks: scan-secrets on PreToolUse Write/Edit, validate-permissions on SessionStart, prompt-based safety checks on Bash commands, and configuration audits on Stop." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Layered security catches issues at multiple lifecycle points — input time, execution time, and completion time." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_30703932 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When scaffolding an enterprise plugin" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Define plugin.json with name, version, commands/agents/hooks/mcpServers paths. 2. Create subdirectories under commands/ grouped by function. 3. Create subdirectories under agents/ grouped by role (orchestration vs specialized). 4. Create skills/ with SKILL.md, references/, examples/, scripts/ subdirs each. 5. Add hooks/hooks.json with PreToolUse, PostToolUse, Stop, SessionStart handlers. 6. Add servers/ with per-domain MCP server implementations. 7. Add lib/ for shared code (core, integrations, utils). 8. Add config/ for environment-specific settings and templates." ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_38427a8a a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When integrating MCP servers into a plugin" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use three MCP servers for separation of concerns: one per domain (e.g., kubernetes for cluster ops, terraform for infrastructure, github-actions for CI/CD). Each server runs as its own process with isolated environment variables." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Domain-separated MCP servers enable parallel operations, independent scaling, and cleaner error isolation." .

oc:kn_499a9901 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When a plugin grows beyond 5-6 items in any category" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not place all skills, agents, or commands in a flat directory structure. Use subdirectories grouped by function or domain (ci/, monitoring/, admin/ for commands; orchestration/, specialized/ for agents)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Flat directories become unmanageable at scale and make it hard to locate specific functionality." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_4b9ddbdf a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating plugin.json for complex plugins" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "json" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Plugin JSON must declare commands as directory paths (e.g., \"./commands/ci\"), agents as directory paths (e.g., \"./agents/orchestration\"), hooks as a single JSON file path, and mcpServers pointing to .mcp.json." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Directory-based references allow auto-discovery of all .md files within, reducing configuration burden." .

oc:kn_6e3ee701 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When referencing any file path within plugin configuration or code" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT} variable in all hook commands, MCP server args, and library requires to ensure paths resolve regardless of where the plugin is installed." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Hard-coded paths break when the plugin is installed in different locations or shared across teams." .

oc:kn_8e3cd31b a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When configuring MCP servers for a plugin" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "json" ;
    oc:directiveContent "MCP server config in .mcp.json uses ${ENV_VAR:-default} syntax for environment variables with optional defaults, and ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT} for referencing server entry points." .

